Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as relation extraction. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the effectiveness of different pooling mechanisms for deep learning models. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with the application of deep learning models for NLP tasks. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a less likely category, but still possible as relation extraction can be seen as a subtask of information retrieval. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with deep learning models.
